# Clean architecture ŌĆö 9 non-negotiable principles (Inversora)

Feature-first layout inspired by Clean / Hexagonal Architecture. These nine principles are **non-negotiable** for new code. Full narrative: `docs/architecture/clean-architecture-principles.md`. Related: ADR-001, ADR-004, `.cursor/rules/testing-strategy.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/screen-reactivity-and-practices.mdc`.

## Layout (dependency arrows inward)

```text
app (composition / Expo Router) ŌåÆ features (use cases + UI) ŌåÆ shared / core
core (domain + ports + adapters) Ōåø features, shared/components
features Ōåø features   (unless documented in ADR-001)
```

Domain and pure rules sit at the center (`core/domain`, `core/scoring`, pure `features/*/utils|models`). I/O and frameworks live in adapters (`core/api`, `core/storage`, `core/analytics`, `core/observability`).

## The nine principles

### 1. Dependency rule

Dependencies point **inward**. Outer layers may import inner ones; never the reverse.

- `app` ŌåÆ `features`, `shared`
- `features` ŌåÆ `shared`, `core`
- `core` must not import `features` or `shared/components`
- No feature ŌåÆ feature imports unless ADR-001 documents an exception

### 2. Pure domain

Domain logic has invariants and no I/O or UI frameworks.

- Put pure rules in `core/domain`, `core/scoring`, or pure `features/*/utils|models`
- No React, Expo Router, AsyncStorage, `fetch`, or analytics inside domain calculators
- Zod schemas for **domain shapes** may live next to domain types; HTTP/transport Zod stays in adapters

### 3. Use cases orchestrate

Use cases coordinate ports and domain; they do not own UI or transport details.

- Prefer `features/*/services` (and domain hooks that only orchestrate) for flows
- Screens compose hooks; they do not inline HTTP or storage
- Inputs/outputs at the use-case boundary are explicit types (often Zod-inferred); keep error codes stable (`AppError` / `AppErrorCode`)

### 4. Ports and adapters

Ports express **needs**; adapters express **technology**.

- Ports: storage contracts, API client surfaces, clock/analytics interfaces used by services
- Adapters: `core/api`, `core/storage`, mappers HTTPŌåödomain, `core/analytics`, Sentry
- Integration tests fake ports; adapter contract tests assert Zod/DTO shapes, error mapping, and port fulfillment (see `testing-strategy.mdc`)

### 5. Explicit composition (Expo)

Wire the app in the composition root ŌĆö **no magic** DI scan / autoload of use cases.

- Compose providers and init in `src/app/_layout.tsx` and `AppProviders` (and thin route files under `src/app`)
- Prefer explicit imports and constructor/factory wiring over hidden global registries
- Do not add Nest-style module scanning or ŌĆ£auto-discover all servicesŌĆØ patterns on the client

### 6. Never treat DTOs as entities / VOs

Transport and read-model DTOs are **not** domain entities or value objects.

- Map at adapter boundaries (`core/api` parsers/mappers); do not leak raw API payloads into screens as ŌĆ£the domainŌĆØ
- Domain types live in `core/domain` (and pure feature models); scoring/application read models (e.g. `FundWithScore`) stay typed outputs ŌĆö do not pretend they are persistence entities
- Do not put UI-only fields on domain types to ŌĆ£save a DTOŌĆØ

### 7. Errors as typed contracts

Prefer stable, typed application errors; reserve unstructured throws for true invariant breaks in pure domain.

- Cross boundary failures: `AppError` + `AppErrorCode` from `core/errors/app-error`
- Adapters map HTTP/storage failures into those codes (contract tests must cover mapping)
- Domain pure functions may throw on broken invariants; do not catch-and-ignore or replace with empty UI state without an explicit code/message path

### 8. Tests by layer

Choose the test from the layer you change (names differ from some hex training slides; Inversora mapping is authoritative):

| Layer | Test |
|-------|------|
| Domain | Unit `*.spec.ts` |
| Use case | Integration `*.integration.spec.ts` + fake ports |
| Adapter | Contract `*.contract.spec.ts` (~100% of touched public surface) |
| Critical UI journey | Few e2e `e2e/*.spec.ts` |

Do not call a pure-function spec an ŌĆ£integrationŌĆØ test. Details: `.cursor/rules/testing-strategy.mdc`, ADR-004.

### 9. Observability as a bridge

Observability crosses layers through **adapters**, not by coupling domain to vendors.

- Product/funnel: `core/analytics` (`trackEvent` / perf marks) ŌåÆ `inversora-api` (see `docs/architecture/analytics.md`)
- Technical health: `core/observability` (Sentry) initialized from the composition root
- Domain and use cases must not import Sentry SDKs or Grafana; metrics/dashboards stay outside the client
- Privacy: anonymous, minimal events only ŌĆö no PII, no free-text questionnaire/assistant content

## Do / Do not (quick)

**Do**

- Keep `src/app` thin; put screens under `features/*/screens`
- Fake ports in use-case tests; contract-test adapters you touch
- Map API Ōåö domain at the edge with Zod

**Do not**

- Import `features/*` from `core` or another feature
- Call network/storage from pure scoring or catalog draft filters
- Pass raw API DTOs through the UI as if they were domain models
- Add hidden service autoloading or vendor SDKs inside domain modules
